# Tutorial Content Conventions

## Format
- Files use **MyST Markdown** for Jupyter Book.
- Use `sphinx-proof` directives (`{prf:assumption}`, `{prf:definition}`, `{prf:theorem}`, etc.) for formal statements.
- Cross-reference with `{prf:ref}`.

## Citations & Sources
When constructing content, cite the sources available in `papers/` and `papers/references.md`.

### PDFs in `papers/`
- Rubin, D. B. (1974). *Estimating causal effects of treatments in randomized and nonrandomized studies.* (`papers/1974 Rubin.pdf`)
- Wooldridge, J. M. (2012). *Introductory Econometrics.* (`papers/2012 Wooldridge - Introductory Econometrics.pdf`)
- Angrist, J. D. & Pischke, J.-S. (2015). *Mastering 'Metrics.* (`papers/Joshua D. Angrist...pdf`)
- Schmidt (2018). *Heterogeneous treatment effects.* (`papers/2018 Schmidt - Heterogeneous.pdf`)

### Key Publications (from `papers/references.md`)
- Athey & Imbens (2016). Recursive partitioning for heterogeneous causal effects.
- Athey, Tibshirani & Wager (2019). Generalized random forests.
- Athey & Wager (2019). Estimating treatment effects with causal forests.
- Austin (2011). Propensity score methods for reducing confounding.
- Breiman (2001). Random forests.
- Breiman et al. (1984). Classification and regression trees.
- Rosenbaum & Rubin (1983). The central role of the propensity score.
- Shalizi (2025). Advanced Data Analysis from an Elementary Point of View.
- Wager & Athey (2018). Estimation and inference of heterogeneous treatment effects using random forests.

### Theory Links
- [Causal ML Book](https://www.causalmlbook.com/)
- [Oxford: Causal Assumptions](https://www.stats.ox.ac.uk/~evans/APTS/causassmp.html)
- [Bookdown: Causal Inference Tutorial](https://bookdown.org/mike/data_analysis/sec-causal-inference.html)
- [Causal Assumptions Guide](https://www.uniqcret.com/post/causal-inference-assumptions-guide)
- [QuantCo: MetaLearners for CATE](https://tech.quantco.com/blog/metalearners)
- [Simpson's Paradox Tutorial](https://www.biostatistics.ca/when-data-lies-simpsons-paradox-a-step-by-step-simulation-code-notebook/)
