Prefer inline parenthetical citations, e.g. (Rubin, 1974) or (Athey & Imbens, 2016). When a link is available, make the citation a hyperlink.

## Notation
- Treatment: $T$ (binary: $T \in \{0,1\}$)
- Outcome: $Y$
- Potential outcomes: $Y(1), Y(0)$
- Covariates: $X$
- Confounder: $C$
- Mediator: $M$
- Observed data: $D = \{(X_i, T_i, Y_i)\}_{i=1}^{n}$
- Propensity score: $\pi(x) = \mathbb{P}(T=1 \mid X=x)$
- Do NOT use $A$ for treatment (use $T$), do NOT use $Z$ for confounder in applied examples (use $C$)
